    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Candidate Name: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.Name }}\nFull Resume Evaluation Report:\n\nConvert this into a professional email ready to send.\n\nYou are a professional email writer and designer.\n\nGenerate a short, clean, professional HTML email.\n\nRules:\n- Keep it concise.\n- No long paragraphs.\n- Show only key highlights.\n- Force white background.\n- Clean card layout.\n- Highlight ATS score clearly.\n- End with:\n\nRegards,\nDeepika\n\n- Use inline CSS only.\n- Output only HTML.\n",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are a professional email writer.\n\nYour task is to convert a resume evaluation report into a clean, well-formatted, professional email ready to be sent to a student.\n\nRules:\n- Start with a personalized greeting using the candidate's name.\n- Keep the tone professional, encouraging, and clear.\n- Present the ATS score clearly near the top.\n- Maintain structured sections with proper spacing.\n- Do NOT use markdown formatting (no ###, no **, no code blocks).\n- Do NOT include analysis explanations.\n- Only output the final email content.\n- End with a soft call-to-action suggesting professional resume optimization support.\n- Keep formatting clean for direct Gmail sending.\n\n\nCandidate Name: {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.Name }}\n\nHere is the resume evaluation report:\n\n{{ $json.output }}\n\nGenerate a professional email with:\n\n1. Greeting\n2. Thank you message\n3. Mention overall ATS score clearly\n4. Present report content cleanly\n5. Encouraging closing note\n6. Soft CTA for resume improvement\n\nDo not add extra commentary.\nOnly output the final email.\n\nYou are a professional email designer and writer.\n\nYour task is to convert a resume evaluation report into a clean, structured, professional HTML email that looks official and premium.\n\nDesign Rules:\n- Use simple HTML only (no external CSS).\n- Wrap content inside a centered container with max-width 600px.\n- Use clean spacing and readable fonts.\n- Use <h2> for main title.\n- Use <strong> for section headings.\n- Use <ul> and <li> for bullet points.\n- Highlight Overall ATS Score clearly near the top.\n- Keep the tone professional and encouraging.\n- End with a branded-style closing section.\n- Do NOT use markdown.\n- Output only valid HTML email body content.\n\n\nYou are a professional email designer.\n\nGenerate a clean, premium HTML email with:\n\n- Forced white background\n- Centered card layout (max-width 620px)\n- Professional typography\n- Precise, concise descriptions\n- Clear spacing\n- Attractive but minimal design\n- Light grey section dividers\n- No long paragraphs\n- Short, sharp bullet points\n\nDesign rules:\n- Use inline CSS only\n- Force background-color: #ffffff on outer wrapper\n- Use a subtle border and soft shadow\n- Highlight ATS score inside a colored box\n- Keep content concise and impactful\n- Output only HTML\n\n"
        }
      },
